---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | productliabilitycalc.com';
const description = 'How productliabilitycalc.com handles your data, including analytics, advertising cookies, and your rights under GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy laws.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: May 18, 2026.</em></p>

  <p>productliabilitycalc.com ("the Site") is operated by The Click Lab ("we," "us," "our"). This Privacy Policy describes what information we collect, how we use it, who we share it with, and what rights you have. We've written it in plain language because the product liability content on this site reaches people who have been injured and need clarity about how their data is handled.</p>

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>Short version: we do not require accounts to use the calculator or read any guide. We do not collect names, addresses, phone numbers, medical records, or any details about your injury beyond what you choose to type into the calculator interface itself (and we don't store calculator inputs on our servers). We use Google Analytics in a low-identifiability configuration to understand traffic patterns. We display ads served by Google AdSense, which uses cookies to show relevant ads. You can opt out of personalized advertising at any time via Google's ad settings.</p>

  <h2>1. Information you provide directly</h2>
  <p>The calculator on this Site is client-side. When you enter defect type, product category, injury severity, economic damages, and state to compute an estimated recovery range, those values are processed in your browser and are not transmitted to our servers. We do not log calculator inputs.</p>
  <p>If you choose to email us, the contents of your email (sender address, body, and any attachments) are received by our email provider and retained for as long as needed to handle the conversation. We don't sell or share that information.</p>

  <h2>2. Information collected automatically</h2>
  <p>Like virtually all modern websites, our hosting provider's edge layer and our analytics provider receive some automatically-transmitted data from every visit. This typically includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your IP address (used to determine approximate location for analytics, discarded after standard retention).</li>
    <li>Browser type and version, operating system, device type, and screen resolution.</li>
    <li>Referrer URL (the page you came from, if any).</li>
    <li>The pages you visit on this Site and how long you spend on each.</li>
    <li>Generic events like page-loads and outbound link clicks.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
  <p>This Site uses a small number of cookies, split by purpose:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Strictly necessary cookies</strong> &mdash; storing privacy preferences themselves.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> &mdash; Google Analytics cookies that distinguish your session from other visitors'.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies</strong> &mdash; Google AdSense cookies for ad personalization. You can opt out via Google's ad settings (see Section 5).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Google Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use Google Analytics 4 in a default-privacy configuration: IP addresses are truncated before storage, ad personalization signals are disabled where possible, and we don't merge GA data with personally identifying user profiles. Google's data handling for Analytics is described at <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>. To opt out of GA entirely, install Google's browser opt-out: <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a>.</p>

  <h2>5. Google AdSense advertising</h2>
  <p>This Site displays ads from Google AdSense (publisher ID pub-6434377544325972). When AdSense renders an ad, Google uses cookies to (a) prevent fraudulent ad clicks, (b) frequency-cap which ads you see, and (c) optionally personalize the ads. You can review and adjust Google's ad personalization settings at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">adssettings.google.com</a> or opt out of third-party ad personalization via <a href="https://aboutads.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aboutads.info</a> or (EU/UK) <a href="https://youronlinechoices.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">youronlinechoices.eu</a>.</p>
  <p>Opting out of personalized advertising does not stop ads from appearing; it stops them being matched to your inferred interests.</p>

  <h2>6. Other third parties</h2>
  <p>We don't sell visitor data. We don't share data with data brokers. Beyond Google Analytics and Google AdSense, the only third parties that may see data about your visit are our hosting provider's CDN and any third-party site you click through to (e.g., agency recall databases, court opinions linked from guides).</p>

  <h2>7. Your rights under GDPR (EEA, UK)</h2>
  <p>If you're in the EEA or UK, the GDPR gives you several rights: access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and objection. To exercise these, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We'll respond within 30 days. Legal basis for our processing is generally (a) your consent (for non-essential cookies) and (b) our legitimate interest in operating, securing, and improving the Site.</p>

  <h2>8. Your rights under CCPA / CPRA (California)</h2>
  <p>California residents have the right to know what personal information we collect, to delete personal information, to opt out of "sale" or "sharing" of personal information, and to non-discrimination for exercising any of these rights. California law treats the use of advertising cookies as a "sale" or "sharing" of information; you can opt out via the Google ad personalization controls in Section 5. To exercise other CCPA rights, contact <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>

  <h2>9. Do Not Track</h2>
  <p>We honor DNT signals to the extent that, when DNT is on, we disable advertising personalization. We don't disable analytics on DNT alone. For analytics-off entirely, use the GA opt-out plugin.</p>

  <h2>10. Children's privacy (COPPA)</h2>
  <p>This Site is intended for adults dealing with product liability matters. We don't knowingly collect information from children under 13. If you believe we have, contact us at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> and we'll delete it.</p>

  <h2>11. Security</h2>
  <p>HTTPS on all pages, no user accounts, no first-party server-side storage of personal data, limited access to admin accounts. Standard practices for a static informational site.</p>

  <h2>12. International transfers</h2>
  <p>Our hosting provider and Google's services may process data outside your country (typically the United States). We rely on standard contractual clauses where required.</p>

  <h2>13. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We update this policy as needed. When we do, we update the "Last updated" date at the top. Material changes will be announced on the home page. Continued use of the Site after a change indicates acceptance.</p>

  <h2>14. Contact</h2>
  <p>Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
